    "Examples of stage 3 and stage 5 are shown in Fig. 11(a Self-Enhancement after generationWith the generated hybrid testbench, implementing a self-enhancement system is necessary to enhance the testbench.",
    "Note that the self-enhancement system does not involve functional correction for the Python checker because there is no additional data to verify the correctness of the testbench in practice.",
    "Code Completion and StandardizationThe Python code from stage 5 is completed by adding a fixed signal interface function, which can read the signals in the.txt file generated by the Verilog driver from stage 4 and send them to the checking function in the Python checker.",
    "For sequential circuits, the Verilog driver must be standardized due to the complexity of the required format, which language models cannot perfectly implement.",
    "For instance, stage 4's prompt requires the driver to export sequential DUT inputs every clock cycle to ensure that the checker has sufficient information, which is often neglected by LLMs."
